            "step_description" : "Preheat Dutch oven on stovetop at medium-high heat. Add oil to pan until hot."
        },
        {
            "step_number" : 3,
            "step_description" : "In batches, sear short ribs on two sides until brown and crispy; remove from pan. Add onion, carrots, celery and garlic to pan; allow vegetables to caramelize."
        },
        {
            "step_number" : 4,
            "step_description" : "Add thyme, bay leaves and tomato paste and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Deglaze pan with beer and cook another 2 to 3 minutes, stirring browned bits from bottom of pan."
        },
        {
            "step_number" : 5,
            "step_description" : "Add short ribs back to pan and add beef stock and maple syrup. Cover, place pan in oven and braise approximately 6 hours, until fork tender."
        },
        {
            "step_number" : 6,
            "step_description" : "Transfer short ribs to a platter. Discard thyme, bay leaves and half of the vegetables. Skim excess fat from surface of sauce. Puree remaining vegetables and sauce until smooth; strain."
        },
        {
            "step_number" : 7,
            "step_description" : "Serve warm short ribs with sauce."
        }
